! STEOM-CCSD STO-3G TightSCF
# DECISIVE formula-correctness test vs my Python complete-active STEOM.
# Formaldehyde sto-3g, frozen core = 2 (O1s+C1s = ORCA default; verify in output),
# COMPLETE active space (DoCISNat false, NActIP = all 6 corr. occ, NActEA = all 4 vir).
# Compare ORCA singlet excitation energies to:
#   Python STEOM (eV): [2.625, 7.374, 12.666, 13.906, 14.814, 17.391, 18.017, 18.263]
#   EOM-EE-CCSD  (eV): [4.034, 9.992, 12.744, 13.513, 14.652, 15.334, 17.610, 17.679]
# If ORCA ~= EOM (4.0 eV lowest) -> Python formula is BUGGED (under-corrects ~1.4 eV).
# If ORCA ~= Python (2.6 eV lowest) -> inherent STEOM!=EOM, Python formula is correct.
%mdci
  nroots 20
  DoSTEOM true
  DoCISNat false
  NActIP 6
  NActEA 4
end
* xyz 0 1
O    0.000000000000     0.000000000000     0.683000000000
C    0.000000000000     0.000000000000    -0.534000000000
H    0.000000000000     0.926000000000    -1.129000000000
H    0.000000000000    -0.926000000000    -1.129000000000
